      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Looking for some each way value with BETTERTHANCASH NZ (2) in the opener. Not too far away last start and came from wider to place here two back. Race fit and should get a nice run from this draw. JILLIBY NITRO (10) heads to Sydney off a last-start Mildura Cup win where he overcame a check and a break to score his third country cup success from his last five starts. Draws deep but has built a strong record in previous visits to this venue. NERANO NZ (7) was too good as a hot favourite at this circuit and distance last time. Draws a little wider and this has more depth but he could go on with it. CAPTAIN BELLASARIO (9) was solid in a good field last time and did a good job to score at this circuit and distance prior. MIKI PINS NZ (8) draws wide but usually races well when third-up so should be close to his peak now.",
